abcd,MHNG-MAM-516.016b,Chiroptera,Molossidae,Tadarida,brasiliensis,mexicana,"(Saussure, 1860)",ind.,ad.,Peau,crâne sous MHNG 516.005,Mexique,Mexico,Amecameca,pied du Popocatepetl,"-98,766667","19,116667",4 localité seulement,"crâne partiel inscrit sous 516.005; attention Baud (1977) le mentionne sous ce numéro-là!
Article de Roguin 1978 (Musées de Genève no 188)
Carter & Dolan (1978, p. 89) assumed that ZMB 2589 “appears to be the only  remaining syntype of Molossus mexicanus”, therefore they designated it as lectotype. Carter &  Dolan ́s assumption and lectotype designation was unjustified, because Baud already in 1977 (p.  208) listed two further syntype specimens from Saussure ́s collection in Museum d ́Histoire  Naturelle Geneve: MHNG 516.16, skin, skull (without braincase) from Ameca[meca], pied du  Popocatepetl, 8.500 ft., and MHNG 516.05, skin with skull inside, from Cofre de Perote,  Veracruz, 13.000 ft.. Saussure (1860: 285) mentioned only one specimen from “Coffre de  Perote, à 13.000 pieds d`altitude” and [unknown number of] additional specimens from “Ameca,  au pied du Popocatepetl, à une altitude de 8.500 pieds”. Thus, ZMB 2589 had come from  Ameca. All mentioned specimens are syntypes.",16,5,1855,17,5,1855,H. de Saussure
